{"id":919,"date":"2022-01-28T18:06:00","date_gmt":"2022-01-28T18:06:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=919"},"modified":"2022-01-26T18:20:24","modified_gmt":"2022-01-26T18:20:24","slug":"start-stop-and-check-the-status-of-network-services","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=919","title":{"rendered":"Start, stop, and check the status of network services"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To start, stop and check status of services, we use a tool called systemctl.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>The systemctl command is a utility which is responsible for examining and controlling the systemd system and service manager. It is a collection of system management libraries, utilities and daemons which function as a successor to the System V init daemon.<\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To demonstrate this, I&#8217;ll install apache or so called httpd with yum package manager.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">sudo yum install httpd<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"start-enable-the-service\">Start\/Enable the service<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To start the service, we simply type<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">systemctl start httpd<\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p>As the name suggest, this will only start the service, but it won&#8217;t survive reboot. To make it so, it starts with the system we use enable <\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">systemctl enable httpd<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>We can also combine these two commands, so we don&#8217;t have to type so much (typing two whole sentences, Am I right?!)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">systemctl --now enable httpd<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"55\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-190.png?resize=640%2C55&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-940\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-190.png?w=867&amp;ssl=1 867w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-190.png?resize=300%2C26&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-190.png?resize=768%2C66&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-190.png?resize=24%2C2&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-190.png?resize=36%2C3&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-190.png?resize=48%2C4&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"stop-disable-the-service\">Stop\/Disable the service<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Same commands apply to opposite action which is stopping and disabling the service<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">systemctl stop httpd<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">systemctl disable httpd<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">systemctl --now disable httpd<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"621\" height=\"55\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-191.png?resize=621%2C55&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-941\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-191.png?w=621&amp;ssl=1 621w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-191.png?resize=300%2C27&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-191.png?resize=24%2C2&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-191.png?resize=36%2C3&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-191.png?resize=48%2C4&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 621px) 100vw, 621px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"check-the-status-of-network-services\">Check the status of network services<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To check if our httpd service is running, we use status <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">systemctl status httpd<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>There is also an option to use is-enabled\/is-disabled, but I find status better overall<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">systemctl is-enabled httpd<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"279\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-192.png?resize=640%2C279&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-942\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-192.png?w=875&amp;ssl=1 875w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-192.png?resize=300%2C131&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-192.png?resize=768%2C334&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-192.png?resize=24%2C10&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-192.png?resize=36%2C16&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-192.png?resize=48%2C21&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>To start, stop and check status of services, we use a tool called systemctl. The [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":840,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[219],"tags":[356,357,220,359,354,358,355],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/rhsa-operate-running-systems.png?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=1","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/919"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcomments&post=919"}],"version-history":[{"count":5,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/919\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":943,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/919\/revisions\/943"}],